†Araxathyris quadrilobata
|
†Araxathyris quadrilobata Abich 1878 (lamp shell)
Rhynchonellata - Athyridida - Athyrididae

PaleoDB taxon number: 199451

Alternative combination: Spirigera quadrilobata

Belongs to Araxathyris according to A. Ghaderi et al. 2015

See also Garbelli and Angiolini 2014, Grunt 1965, Grunt 1986 and Yousefirad et al. 2013

Sister taxa: Araxathyris abichi, Araxathyris beipeiensis, Araxathyris bruntoni, Araxathyris costalis, Araxathyris dilatatus, Araxathyris felina, Araxathyris glossexserta, Araxathyris indentatus, Araxathyris jalaidensis, Araxathyris jiangyouensis, Araxathyris longa, Araxathyris protea, Araxathyris rhombiformis, Araxathyris sinensis, Araxathyris timorensis, Araxathyris tongluensis, Araxathyris undulata, Araxathyris yuananensis

Ecology: stationary low-level epifaunal suspension feeder

Environments: deep subtidal ramp (2 collections), carbonate (1), open shallow subtidal (1)

Average measurements (in mm): shell 31.8 x 34.9

Age range: 254.0 to 252.3 Ma

Distribution:

• Permian of Azerbaijan (3 collections), China (1), Iran (19)

Total: 23 collections including 24 occurrences
